Distribution. Up until now,
Bachia didactyla
is known from only two localities (
Fig. 4
), both situated in Chapada dos Parecis , a huge plateau ( 300–800 m above sea level) in Midwestern Brazil , between the headwaters of upper rio Paraguay (Platina Basin) and upper rio Tapajós (Amazon Basin). Extending from eastern Mato Grosso State to eastern Rondônia, the plateau is situated in a contact region between two major vegetation zones: the open Cerrado from Central Brazil , and the southernmost limits of the forested Amazonia domain. Large tracts of interfluvial savannas originally covered most of the summit surfaces of the Parecis plateau (
IBGE 1993
;
SEPLAN 2010
). Habitat data are not available for specimens collected during faunal monitoring activities in the region of the hydroeletric powerplant AHE Cachoeirão, rio Juruena, in Sapezal municipality, state of Mato Grosso.
